\title{Opennirscap Build}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Build an OpenNIRScap 24-channel fNIRS brain cap from open-source hardware — Altium conversion, BOM sourcing, PCB fab, assembly, firmware flash}

\subtree{
\title{OpenNIRScap Build}
\p{Open-source 24-channel fNIRS wearable brain cap. Kim et al. 2025, University of Toronto.}

\subtree{
\title{Source}
\ul{
\li{Repo: https://github.com/tonykim07/fNIRS}
\li{Paper: https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.20509}
\li{License: BSD-3-Clause}
\li{Hardware: Altium Designer files (PcbDoc, SchDoc)}
\li{Firmware: STM32 C (STM32L476RET6)}
\li{Software: Python Flask-SocketIO GUI}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Architecture}
\ul{
\li{24 detector modules (VBPW34S photodiode + AD8618 TIA, 25mm circular PCB)}
\li{8 dual-wavelength source emitters (VSMD66694: 660nm + 940nm)}
\li{1 ECU (STM32L476 + 8x TMUX1104 analog MUX + PCA9685 PWM, 112x112mm PCB)}
\li{35mm source-detector separation (cortical depth sensitivity)}
\li{1 kHz effective sampling, 52.3 dB SNR, 12-bit ADC}
\li{USB isolated (ADUM4160), LiPo powered (1100mAh, >5hr)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Blocker: Altium to Gerber Conversion}
\p{Repo has Altium .PcbDoc source files, no exported gerbers or CSV BOMs.}

\subtree{
\title{PCBs to convert}
\pre{\startverb
| Project | File | Description |
|---------|------|-------------|
| fNIRS_sensor_module | SensorModulePCB.PcbDoc | 25mm circular, combined emitter+detector |
| fNIRS_ECU | fNIRS_PCB.PcbDoc | 112x112mm main control board |
| DetectorOptode | DetectorOptode.PcbDoc | Detector-only variant |
| SourceOptode | SourceOptode.PcbDoc | Source-only variant |
| STLINK_Breakout | STLINK_Breakout.PcbDoc | Programming adapter |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Conversion approaches (in order of preference)}
\ol{
\li{\strong{KiCad 8 built-in importer} — File > Import > Altium .PcbDoc. Best fidelity. Needs KiCad installed.}
\li{\strong{altium2kicad} (Perl, 933 stars) — \code{\startverb perl convertpcb.pl file.PcbDoc\stopverb}. Repo: thesourcerer8/altium2kicad. Needs \code{\startverb unpack.pl\stopverb} first.}
\li{\strong{Altium 365 Viewer} (free web) — View online, manual export. No CLI.}
\li{\strong{GitHub Issue} — Ask authors to export gerbers. Repo is active (last push 2026-03).}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Attempted and failed}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb altium-cli\stopverb} (Rust, akiselev) — broken workspace deps, won't build}
\li{\code{\startverb pyaltium\stopverb} — crashes on Python 3.14 (missing dateutil dep)}
\li{\code{\startverb altium2kicad\stopverb} unpack.pl worked but convertpcb.pl couldn't find unpacked files}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Next step}
\p{Install KiCad 8 (\code{\startverb brew install --cask kicad\stopverb} or \code{\startverb nix shell nixpkgs#kicad\stopverb}), import PcbDoc, export gerbers + BOM + CPL from KiCad.}
}
}

